    "chemicalDescription": [
      "sr-(Clostridium Botulinum Polypeptide-2 Arginyl Oligopeptide-192 Clostridium Botulinum Polypeptide-1 Oligopeptide-192 Oligopeptide-193) is a single chain recombinant peptide produced by fermentation in E. coli. The starting gene is synthesized by the fusion of the gene from sr-Clostridium Botulinum Polypeptide-2, Oligopeptide-192, sr-Clostridium Botulinum Polypeptide-1, and Oligopeptide-193 with the initiation code for arginine. The fusion peptide contains 492 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence from the 20 standard amino acids."
    ],
